The JQL function 'withinCalendarHours' filters issues that are currently within calendar hours or outside calendar hours.

Quoted from [JSD-3159|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSD-3159]:
{quote}
A new feature, rom JSD Server 3.0.4 and JSD Cloud 3.1.0-OD-05 is that there is a new JQL function "withinCalendarHours".

This function will allow JQL searching and Queues to be constructed that will either show issue that are currently within calendar hours or outside calendar hours.
{quote}

However there are no further documentation or examples of the function, as in the [Advanced searching|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwareserver073/advanced-searching-861256227.html] guide.
